Background information
----------------------

MIREX stands for MapReduce Information Retrieval Experiments. MIREX 
provides a simple and flexible solution for doing large-scale 
information retrieval experiments.  Please cite the following paper
if you use MIREX in your scientific work:

    Djoerd Hiemstra and Claudia Hauff. MIREX: MapReduce Information
Retrieval Experiments. CTIT Technical Report, Centre for Telematics 
and Information Technology, University of Twente, ISSN 1381-3625,
2010


Install
-------

Change the 'value' attribute of  <property name="hadoop" /> such 
that it contains your Hadoop distribution, then run ant. 
The code was tested on Hadoop version 0.19.2


Usage
-----

Run anchor text extraction as follows:

% hadoop jar mirex-0.1.jar nl.utwente.mirex.AnchorExtract \
  /user/hadoop/ClueWeb09_English/*/ /user/hadoop/ClueWeb09_Anchors

Then, run a TREC evaluation by:

% hadoop jar mirex-0.1.jar nl.utwente.mirex.TrecRun \
  /user/hadoop/ClueWeb09_Anchors/* /user/hadoop/TrecOut \
  /user/hadoop/wt09-topics.txt


